## Endpoint Memo

- `[VERIFIED]` Why the primary endpoint is the right first theorem-facing
  window:
  the only locally frozen theorem floor remains suitable weak /
  Leray-Hopf plus LEI with the CKN/Lin epsilon-regularity contradiction
  package, so the honest first endpoint is concentration-style
  endpoint-exclusion on that inherited ledger rather than a new framework.
- `[INFERRED]` Why the backup endpoint is the right reserve:
  continuation / norm-level control is a stricter reserve that the record
  allows only after a candidate already behaves like near-coercive control.
  Keeping exactly this reserve prevents an artificially rigid single line
  without reopening a soft endpoint portfolio.
- `[VERIFIED]` What kinds of gains count at this interface:
  only gains that return, after full debt, to a smaller effective coefficient
  on the full localized `I_flux[phi]` bundle inside the inherited LEI package.
- `[VERIFIED]` What kinds of gains are decorative:
  prettier identities before localization;
  derivative-count or exponent language with no same-ledger cash-out;
  variable changes that only redistribute the same burden;
  or gains that require leaving the fixed solution class or cutoff protocol.

## Burden-Ledger Memo

- `[VERIFIED]` Baseline burden in concrete theorem-facing language:
  the full localized LEI cutoff-flux bundle
  `I_flux[phi] = ∬ (|u|^2 + 2p) u · ∇phi`
  under one shared CKN-style cutoff protocol.
- `[VERIFIED]` Admissible gain notion:
  positive-margin smaller effective coefficient on that same full bundle after
  pressure recovery, projection/CZ, commutator, reconstruction, and
  admissibility debt are charged.
- `[INFERRED]` Burden currencies:
  derivative count records whether a derivative reduction survives back to the
  live LEI estimate;
  locality records whether the gain acts on the full bundle or only a local
  surrogate;
  cancellation records exact sign/null-structure savings on the same bundle;
  integrability records any space/exponent improvement awaiting transfer;
  pressure recoverability records pressure-reentry and projection debt;
  admissibility records host-class and regularity debt;
  compactness input records any extra extraction/rigidity machinery imported;
  scaling compatibility records whether the claim respects the inherited LEI /
  CKN scaling and shared cutoff protocol.
- `[INFERRED]` Same-currency comparison is sufficient when two candidate claims
  act on the same full `I_flux[phi]` object under the same solution class,
  localization regime, and charged debt.
- `[INFERRED]` A transfer lemma is mandatory whenever the claimed gain lives in
  any different currency from the baseline burden. Without an explicit
  theorem-level transfer back to a smaller full-bundle coefficient, the claim
  remains unresolved and does not count.

## Anti-Repackaging And Prior-Art Memo

- `[INFERRED]` `equivalent redistribution`:
  after localization, pressure recovery, reconstruction, admissibility debt,
  and any claimed transfer, the candidate leaves the same full `I_flux[phi]`
  burden with no positive-margin smaller coefficient.
- `[INFERRED]` `ambiguous redistribution`:
  the candidate identifies one exact ledger cell where a gain may exist, but
  it does not yet produce a same-currency cash-out or an explicit transfer
  lemma to the frozen theorem burden.
- `[INFERRED]` `potentially live mechanism change`:
  after full debt, the candidate either directly lowers the effective
  coefficient on the full `I_flux[phi]` bundle by a positive margin or names a
  specific transfer lemma whose conclusion is exactly that same gain.
- `[INFERRED]` Minimum evidence needed to avoid immediate prior-art absorption:
  one nearest comparator on the local record;
  one sentence naming the shared exact structure;
  one exact mathematical delta;
  one improved frozen ledger entry after debt;
  and one same-currency cash-out or explicit transfer lemma.
- `[INFERRED]` Frozen prior-art audit format for later candidate packets:
  `candidate reformulation / unknown`;
  `nearest known comparator on the repository record`;
  `shared exact structure already present there`;
  `claimed mathematical delta`;
  `baseline burden entry being improved`;
  `debt ledger entries charged immediately`;
  `same-currency cash-out on full I_flux[phi] or explicit transfer lemma`;
  `anti-repackaging classification`;
  `prior-art absorption verdict`.

