+  on theorem-floor objects inside the fixed Eulerian package:
+  the intense set `E_r(t) = {x in B_r(x_*) : |omega(x,t)| >= r^-2}` on
+  `B_r(x_*) x [t_* - r^2, t_*]`, together with direction data on that set.
+- [VERIFIED] No named proxy class is frozen anywhere in the required local
+  record for this geometry route.
+- [INFERRED] The honest admissibility freeze is therefore:
+  `direct suitable-weak / LEI admissible`, not proxy-based.
+- [INFERRED] The important caveat is different:
+  the route is transport-dependent rather than genuinely geometry-native on the
+  theorem floor. Its only live content is the hoped-for persistence of
+  direction coherence along a coherent tube family across the diffusion-scale
+  window.
+
+### 2. Exact bridge burden back to the theorem floor
+
+- [INFERRED] Because no proxy class is honestly frozen here, there is no adopted
+  proxy-to-floor bridge ledger.
+- [INFERRED] The real burden sits inside the theorem floor itself and has three
+  inseparable parts:
+  1. match coherent intense components across the full `r^2` window inside the
+     neutral Eulerian package without tube-adapted relocalization, threshold
+     retuning, or hidden axis fitting;
+  2. propagate direction coherence on that moving intense set without importing
+     the stronger `nabla xi`-type derivative control that the local record
+     treats as a return to known direction-regularity burden; and
+  3. turn that persistence information into a smaller criterion-scale input or
+     a smaller full-stretching contribution on the inherited theorem floor.
+- [VERIFIED] The local record already identifies exactly these burdens as the
+  missing mechanism behind the hybrid's failure:
+  Eulerian component matching,
+  diffusion-scale persistence,
+  hidden relocalization,
+  and `nabla xi`-type debt.
+- [INFERRED] If one tried to reinterpret those burdens as a de facto proxy
+  bridge, it would already look `theorem-scale`.
+  But the cleaner Step-1 ruling is that no proxy class has actually been earned.
+
+### 3. Primary comparator
+
+- [VERIFIED] The local prior-art benchmark with the strongest theorem footprint
+  is the Constantin-Fefferman / direction-regularity family.
+- [VERIFIED] The Step-3 observable table already says
+  `vorticity-direction coherence` is the comparator that tests whether the
+  hybrid adds anything beyond prior-art benchmark material.
+- [INFERRED] I therefore freeze exactly one primary comparator:
+  `vorticity-direction coherence`
+  in the Constantin-Fefferman / direction-regularity neighborhood.
+- [VERIFIED] Shared structure already present there:
+  stretching-facing vorticity-direction coherence on the intense set, aimed at
+  the scalar stretching factor `xi . S xi`.
+- [INFERRED] Claimed mathematical delta of the proposed route:
+  add a dynamic persistence ingredient, via coherent tube persistence on
+  intense regions, so that direction coherence is not merely a static criterion
+  hypothesis but a dynamically persistent input that could reduce a full
+  stretching term, especially an exterior/inter-scale contribution or a
+  localization-evolution cost.
+
+### 4. Comparator absorption check
+
+- [VERIFIED] The repository already warns that direction regularity is prior
+  art and that importing stronger `nabla xi`-type control just collapses the
+  route back into that comparator family.
+- [VERIFIED] The repository also warns that tube persistence without an honest
+  dynamic bridge collapses to descriptive geometry.
+- [INFERRED] So the proposed delta is very narrow even before package choice:
+  it survives only if tube persistence gives a genuinely dynamic,
+  theorem-facing gain beyond the direction-coherence comparator.
+- [INFERRED] The local dynamic audits instead say the hybrid is only
+  `informative but dynamically weak`, while all audited candidates fail before
+  later representation work.
+- [INFERRED] This means prior-art overlap, not proxy failure, is already the
+  sharper Step-1 screen:
+  the shared comparator structure is concrete, but the claimed delta is only a
+  transport narrative unless a persistence mechanism is supplied.
+
+### 5. Earliest honest obstruction
+
+- [INFERRED] The earliest honest obstruction is
+  `descriptive-convenience obstruction, branch should stop before package selection`.
+- [INFERRED] Reason:
+  a singular admissibility standard and comparator can be frozen, but the only
+  claimed gain over the direction-coherence comparator is an unearned
+  transport-dependent persistence story rather than a frozen theorem-facing
+  mathematical mechanism.
+- [INFERRED] The neutral Eulerian package remains useful only as a killed
+  secondary comparator:
+  it shows that the route becomes dynamically weak unless one imports exactly
+  the stronger tracking or derivative structure that Step 1 was supposed to
+  avoid.
+
+## Conclusion
+
+- Admissibility standard frozen:
+  `direct suitable-weak / LEI admissible`
+- Bridge burden verdict:
+  `no adopted proxy bridge; the real burden is theorem-floor transport dependence`
+- Primary comparator frozen:
+  `vorticity-direction coherence` in the
+  `Constantin-Fefferman / direction-regularity` neighborhood
+- Exact claimed delta:
+  add an NS-specific dynamic persistence bridge from coherent tube families to
+  criterion-scale direction input and full stretching
+- Step-1 verdict signal:
+  the branch fails by prior-art absorption / descriptive convenience before
+  package selection
+
+## Dead Ends / Corrections
+
+- [VERIFIED] Earlier in this report, I briefly framed the hybrid as if it lived
+  on a named proxy class.
+- [INFERRED] After explicitly checking the required local record for any such
+  named proxy class, I rejected that framing.
+  The repository does not freeze one.
+  The cleaner admissibility reading is direct theorem-floor definability plus a
+  transport-dependent persistence burden.

